<span id="freeTextContainer9592227909077137608"><br/><br/>This book is so good! ❤<br/><br/><img src='https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1487259897ra/21992861.gif' alt=' ' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/>I cried in this book because of something sad and then it wasn&apos;t sad because of reasons but I&apos;m not sure because of . . . <br/><br/>I cried because of the REVELATIONS, REVELATIONS, REVELATIONS! They were so freaking awesome that I can&apos;t evennnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnn! <br/><br/><b>
  <blockquote>I&apos;ve seen Steelheart bleed.<br/>And I will see him bleed again.</blockquote>
</b><br/><br/>Yes, we all know that line. Those that have read the book. This is what David thinks when 10 years ago his father was killed by Steelheart. Now </span>
  <span id="freeText9592227909077137608" style="display:none"><br><br>This book is so good! ❤<br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1487259897ra/21992861.gif" alt=" " class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>I cried in this book because of something sad and then it wasn't sad because of reasons but I'm not sure because of . . . <br><br>I cried because of the REVELATIONS, REVELATIONS, REVELATIONS! They were so freaking awesome that I can't evennnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnnn! <br><br><b>
