        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1575276873" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10360199307315574610">My relationship with The Reckoners series is like a relationship with someone you love deeply, despite the fact that they’re chewing out loudly. Brandon Sanderson is one of my favourite authors and I so wish he treated this story like he treated The Mistborn series. But when you’re fed up with “the greater good” and “great power comes with great responsibility”, a story about superpowered people who are using their powers for their own benefit comes like a breath of fresh air.<br/><br/>However, compared t</span>
  <span id="freeText10360199307315574610" style="display:none">My relationship with The Reckoners series is like a relationship with someone you love deeply, despite the fact that they’re chewing out loudly. Brandon Sanderson is one of my favourite authors and I so wish he treated this story like he treated The Mistborn series. But when you’re fed up with “the greater good” and “great power comes with great responsibility”, a story about superpowered people who are using their powers for their own benefit comes like a breath of fresh air.<br /><br />However, compared to, let’s say Vin (Mistborn), the characters were kinda plain :( I would have loved a more adult take, but that's just me.<br /><br />Still, 5 stars.</span>
