    <a title="Peter Topside" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/103311536-peter-topside"><img alt="Peter Topside" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1597669259p2/103311536.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3931280212?book_show_action=true">May 08, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Peter Topside" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Peter Topside" href="/user/show/103311536-peter-topside">Peter Topside</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/43633995-steelheart">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3931280212" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11722447782764288301">This was a lot of fun. I thoroughly enjoyed the concept of superpowered beings (Epics) ruling over this new version of society and the rag-tag group (Reckoners) working underground, attempting to defeat them. I didn&apos;t necessarily love any of the characters, but they each brought something unique to the table. I also felt that the dialogue ran long at times, while neglecting some of the more desired details of the environment and hierarchy of Epics at large, but that all may just be my personal p</span>
  <span id="freeText11722447782764288301" style="display:none">This was a lot of fun. I thoroughly enjoyed the concept of superpowered beings (Epics) ruling over this new version of society and the rag-tag group (Reckoners) working underground, attempting to defeat them. I didn't necessarily love any of the characters, but they each brought something unique to the table. I also felt that the dialogue ran long at times, while neglecting some of the more desired details of the environment and hierarchy of Epics at large, but that all may just be my personal preference. The story is solid, the writing is great, and I am making sequels a priority. Bravo!</span>
  <a data-text-id="11722447782764288301" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

